>
> No, but you need to seal the hole in the heat exchanger. And the heat will
> work fine on the freeway, just not at idle.
> Use aluminum flashing and silicone, or aluminum "bumper repair" tape. I've
> got the tape on the Guac right now.
>
> If the other tube is sticking up into the engine compartment you need to
> seal that as well.
